The paper deals with kernelization of a graph problem, specifically Planar Dominating Set and its parameterized version Planar Nonblocker, which are both in the domain of computational complexity and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are all likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of discharging method, which is a technique in graph theory and combinatorics, making cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics) a possible sub-category as well. Finally, the paper presents a result on the size of dominating sets in graphs, which falls under the domain of graph theory and could be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as well.
